A policeman has been arrested in connection with a cash-in-transit heist committed in Kraaifontein in Tuesday night, the Hawks said on Wednesday.The suspects held the guards at gunpoint in Wabrug Road and stole an undisclosed amount of cash before fleeing the scene, spokesperson Lieutenant Lloyd Ramovha said in a statement. Investigations into the robbery led to the arrest of a 33-year-old police constable at his residence in Khayelitsha. One bag containing cash was recovered. The policeman was stationed at the Nyanga police station and allegedly used an official vehicle in the heist. The five other robbers were still at large. The constable was expected to appear in the Kuils River Magistrate s Court on Friday.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.